benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/tags - Retrieve bundle tags

covered: Valid Request: Happy path and multiple valid parameter combinations are covered (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05, TC18).
Empty Response: Bundle with no tags returns an empty array (TC06).
Query Parameters: Comprehensive coverage of valid and invalid query parameters (includedDeleted, audit, extra params, missing audit) across TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05, TC09, TC10, TC14, TC18.
Authorization: Tests for missing and invalid authentication tokens (TC12, TC13).
Error Handling/Status Codes: Covers 404, 400, 401, 503/504, and 400/422 error scenarios (TC07, TC08, TC09, TC11, TC12, TC13, TC14).
Performance/Load: Handling large data sets, slow dependencies, concurrency (TC15, TC16, TC19, TC20).
Regression/Backward Compatibility: Includes tests for deleted-tages when includedDeleted=false (TC17) and no-audit-parameter compatibility (TC18).
gaps: Pagination: No tests covering pagination behavior for large datasets.
Authorization: No test for 403 Forbidden (insufficient privileges).
Caching Behavior: No tests asserting ETag/Cache-Control headers.
Rate Limiting: No explicit tests asserting 429 responses under burst load.
Internal Server Error: No test simulating 500 Internal Server Error; only 503/504 available.
Extended injection tests: Additional parameter injections beyond audit and bundleId could be explored.
recommendations: Add pagination tests for page size, page boundaries, and total counts when datasets are large.
Add an explicit 403 Forbidden test for insufficient privileges.
Add tests for caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) and cache validation behavior.
Add rate-limiting tests to verify correct handling of bursts and 429 responses.
Add a test for 500 Internal Server Error scenarios to validate server-side failure handling.
Expand coverage with more diverse edge cases: invalid characters in bundleId across all endpoints, and validation of all input parameter types.
Consider adding end-to-end observability checks: logs and metrics for errors and latency.
